25 "§ 74D-5.1. Position of Director created.
26 The position of Director of the Alarm Security Systems Licensing Board is hereby created
27 within the Department of Public Safety. The Secretary of Public Safety shall appoint a person to
28 fill this full-time position. The Director's duties shall be to administer the directives contained in
29 this Chapter and the rules promulgated adopted by the Board to implement this Chapter and to
30 carry out the administrative duties incident to the functioning of the Board in order to actively
31 police the alarm systems security systems industry to insure ensure compliance with the law in
32 all aspects. The Director may issue a temporary grant or denial of a request for registration subject
33 to final action by the Board at its next regularly scheduled meeting.
34 "§ 74D-5.2. Investigative powers of the Secretary of Public Safety.
35 The Secretary of Public Safety shall have the power to investigate or cause to be investigated
36 any complaints, allegations, or suspicions of wrongdoing or violations of this Chapter involving
37 individuals unlicensed, licensed, or to be licensed, under this Chapter. Any investigation
38 conducted pursuant to this section is deemed confidential and is not subject to review under
39 G.S. 132-1 until the investigation is complete and a report is presented to the Board. However,
40 the report may be released to the licensee after the investigation is complete but before the report
41 is presented to the Board.
42 "§ 74D-6. Denial of a license or registration.
43 Upon a finding that the applicant meets the requirements for licensure or receipt of an
44 application for licensure or registration under this Chapter, G.S. 74D-8, the Board shall determine
45 whether the applicant shall receive the license or registration applied for. The grounds for denial
46 include:include all of the following:
47 (1) Commission of some act which, if committed by a registrant or licensee,
48 would be grounds for the suspension or revocation of a registration or license
49 under this Chapter;Chapter.
